Hundreds lined up for the long-awaited grand opening of McDonald's on Moscow's  Pushkin Square.
Musicians played and dancers danced.
The world's newest, largest  McDonald's then proceeded to ring up 30,000 meals on 27 cash registers, breaking the  opening day record for McDonald's worldwide.
Generally accustomed to clerks who  snarl, Muscovites got a first-hand look at efficient, fast and friendly service.
For most  customers it was their first experience with a hamburger.
Initial reactions were favorable.
This is the first of twenty McDonald's planned for the Soviet Union.
It brought to 52 the  number of countries where McDonald's operates. 
